Mid-Term Project - Hima Pragnya Jonnalagadda¶

Overview¶
  1. Use Medicare CCLF Claims from Syntegra dataset to answer key business questions
  2. Extra credit for building up on the questions below (additional questions + answers)
  3. One Jupyter notebook solution with clear Python code and all cell outputs available
  4. At least two data quality checks

Step 0. Prepare raw input datasets¶

Here we will 1) load original datasets, 2) remove unused columns, 3) de-duplicate rows, and 4) join datasets, not necessarily in this order

Assumptions:

  1. Claim ID (cur_clm_uniq_id) represents one claim, which may or may not have more than one code (code could be HCPCS/CPT, diagnosis, procedure...)
  2. There is a one-to-many relationship between patient IDs (bene_mbi_id) and claim IDs (cur_clm_uniq_id), i.e. each claim is unique to one patient, but one patient can have more than one claim

Think about business insights in terms of key decisions that sales and marketing leadership needs to make, e.g. sales force, sales force tactics (how to word the messaging sent out to HCPs), patient experience¶

Insights :¶

  1. The number of cardiac claims has increased steadily over the past three years, from 3,562 in 2016 to 4,823 in 2018.

  2. The percentage of cardiac claims to total claims has remained relatively stable, at around 12-13%.

  3. The percentage of non-cardiac claims to total claims has decreased slightly, from 88% in 2016 to 87% in 2018

These trends suggest that the prevalence of heart disease is on the rise.

Sales leaders should consider allocating more resources to selling to healthcare providers (HCPs) who treat cardiac patients. This could involve hiring more sales representatives with experience in the cardiac market, or training existing sales representatives on the latest cardiac products and services.

The sales representatives should highlight to the HCPSs, the benefits of their products and services for cardiac patients.¶
The representatives can also show these trends of claims and scientific evidence on how effective is their product in improving patient outcomes.¶

Sales leaders should also focus on developing sales strategies that are tailored to the needs of cardiac patients.

B Expected Technical Output:¶

i. A 100% stacked bar graph

ii. Each bar represents a year

iii. Each bar consists of percentage of CVM and non-CVM claims

5. How would you determine which sales tactic is best for which segment?¶

Insights :¶

  1. From the figures analyzed, Its is clear that significant number of HCPs are making just one claim through all the years
  2. And the numbers increased substantially between the years for all the categories.

Disease Aware¶

  1. Since these HCPs are aware of the disease and may not have extensive experience with the pharmaceutical product, the objective should be to increase product awareness and knowledge among HCPs in this segment. The sales tactic would be to focus on educational initiatives. Provide comprehensive information about the disease, the benefits of the product, and any recent updates or advancements to the HCPs

Trialists¶

These HCPs have shown interest by making in 2-4 claims. The objective should be to build on the existing interest and convert trialists into regular prescribers. Provide the HCPs with more in-depth clinical data, highlight the trial outcomes, and emphasize the product's efficacy and safety profile.

Rising stars¶

These HCPs are gaining experience with the pharmaceutical product. The objective os sales head should be to foster loyalty and encourage these rising stars to become consistent prescribers. Offer support through continued medical education programs, share success stories from peers, and provide resources to address any concerns they may have.

High- Volume prescibers¶

The Pharma company should focus on maintaining strong relationships with high-volume prescribers. They should retain and nurture relationships with these key prescribers to sustain and potentially increase prescription volumes. Provide them with exclusive benefits, such as early access to new information, personalized support. Acknowledge their significant contribution to prescription volume.

vii.Which marketing and promotion strategies would focus on the patients?¶

Insights¶

Patient Age group (18-59)¶

  1. This Age groups potrays less number of cvm claims when compared to other patient age groups and shows an increasing trend in the number of claims over the years (321 in 2016, 383 in 2017, and 422 in 2018).
  2. The sales and marketing head of the pharma company can Target online platforms to reach the younger demographic. Use social media channels for awareness campaigns to create educational content

Patient Age group (60-69)¶

  1. This age group of patients made higher claims related to the cardiac diseases.
  2. The pharma company can conduct events or webinars addressing health concerns specific to this age group and collaborate with senior centers to provide educational materials and support.

Patient Age group (70-79)¶

  1. This group exhibits a significant increase in claims from 1043 in 2016 to 1757 in 2018.
  2. Reach out through targeted print materials, as this age group may still respond well to traditional forms of communication and Collaborate with healthcare providers to organize health check-up camps or programs.

Patient Age group (80+)¶

  1. Patients above 80 significantly made less cardiac claims when comapred to the agr groups (60-69) & (70-79)
  2. Marketing strategies for this group can be to develop programs that support caregivers of elderly patients and conduct informational sessions in assisted living facilities.
